Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a medium #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat. Add the @sliced mushrooms{240%g} to the pan and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{4-5%mins}, stirring
occasionally. Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%min}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}. Pop the @creme fraiche{150%g},
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and olive oil for the sauce into a
medium #bowl{}. Mix together, then season to taste with salt and pepper.

> This creamy sauce forms the base of your white pizza - no tomato sauce needed!

Pop the @pizza bases{2} onto a #cutting board{}. Spread the creamy sauce equally
over the pizza bases, leaving a 1cm border around the edge.

Once the garlic mushrooms are cooked, divide them between the pizza bases and
scatter over the Cheddar cheese.

When the oven is hot, slide the pizzas directly onto the middle rack and bake
until the base is golden and the cheese has melted and is bubbly, ~{10-12%mins}.

Transfer the pizzas to your #serving plates{} and cut into slices. Sprinkle
over the @truffle zest{1%tsp} and finish with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g}.
Enjoy!